We recommended that:

Management create an inventory committee to conduct the annual inventory taking and prepare the RPCPPE completely indicating all the data required and identify each property individually and refrain from using generic classifications of the PPE;

Submit a copy of the RPCPPE to the Office of the Auditor not later than January 31st of each year as provided in Volume II of the New Government Accounting System (NGAS) to facilitate verification of the inventory report;

The Accounting Unit and GSO work together in the reconciliation of the discrepancies of PPE balances per physical count and accounting records; and

The Accounting Unit and GSO maintain the prescribed property records and see to it that these independent but related records are regularly reconciled to attain the LGU’s financial reporting objective of issuing timely and reliable financial reports/statements.

