We recommended the following:
1.	Management incorporate projects in the Annual Invest Plan that is within the scope allowable as identified in social development, economic development and environmental management;
2.	The Local Development Council monitor the implementation of the projects as incorporated in the Annual Investment Plan;
3.	The Municipal Engineer coordinate with the departments concerned to fast track the implementation of the projects; and
4.	The Local Chief Executive shall ensure compliance with the responsibilities provided for in paragraph 5.0 of DILG and DBM Joint Circular No. 2017-1 to achieve desirable socio-economic development and environmental outcomes.

We recommended that:
1.	Management include representatives from the private sector, academe and recognized and/or accredited nongovernment organizations as well as women associations as member of the municipality’s GFPS Execom and establish formal TWG for the LGU’s GFPS;
2.	The GFPS gather and build up sex-disaggregated data and GAD related information that can be source in the agencies suggested by Joint Circular No. 2013-1 such as the NSO, NSCB, DSWD and DepED. Maintain and establish GAD database to serve as basis for gender-responsive planning, programming and policy formulation;
3.	The LGU GFPS shall monitor the implementation of the annual GPB and assess the status of the LGU’s institutional mechanism on gender mainstreaming annually. It shall also ensure that the GAD Objective and Activity must respond to the gender issue identified in the GPB.

